<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100660041019367></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100660041019367><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=?class=4&mid=100660041019367>Suggestion on Bard Equipment</a> <a id=fs8 href=?class=4&mid=100660041019367#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=121906><span id= >QuemnWyndrunner</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Nov 24th 6:13 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off, this is coming from a lvl 57 Bard. This was my first character that I really enjoyed, and I've been playing him since the first day Brell Serilis opened.<br><br>I recommend going with Charisma after you get your mez and charm songs, but keep it around 120-150. The rest? go for AC! <br><br>I've tested charisma bonuses many, many times. Mezzes work better over 120, but don't seem to do much, if anything after 150.<br>&nbsp;<br>Quemn Wyndrunner<br>57 Bard Brell Serilis<br>21 Bard Percival</td></tr>
