	   <tr><td colspan=2>Currently, my bard is level 42, and I have soloed and grouped with every strategy I can think of.  Bards are charisma dependent when it comes to their mezzes and charms.  None of the other songs really require charisma.  Depending on your style of play, you should get gear that adds to strength and dex if you're planning on doing a great deal of melee, agility and stamina if you're planning on getting hit a lot, dex if you're planning on using instruments primarily (minorly affects missed notes, but not as much as skill), and charisma and dex if you're planning on charming and mezzing.<br><br>Some enchanters will tell you that charisma doesn't affect charms and mezzes to enough of a degree to really bother with it more than some other stats.  However, enchanters, are not having to refresh their mezes or charms as often as bards, due to their spells having a longer duration.  I intend to perform a series of tests on the reliability of bardic charm with charismas of 90 (my base), 100, 120, 150, and possibly 175.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
