	   <tr><td colspan=2>Umm...really? Regen items are useful on bards? Never would've guessed...<br><br>= P<br><br>Regen items are 'great ways to level' for anyone that can wear them. Increasing the amount of HP regenerated while sitting reduces downtime, as there's a shorter amount of time between kills. In actuality, bards have the least use for a regen item out of any class that can use them, since they acquire the ability to regenerate at a decent rate from level 6 when they get Hymn of Restoration. Finally, of the items that grant regeneration on a permanent basis, the cheapest I can think of (Iksar BP, 5pts per tick or so) runs probably about 10k, making them somewhat out of reach for non-twinks.<br><br>Point: while all your points are true, they seem rather unecessary.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
