	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, I know that around level 20 when warriors and other tank classes start to pull away in AC/HP terms, some bards think they're the stuff and try to tank and solo every mob in sight. I assure you, your HP's are nothing compared to a tank, and bards are not designed to tank or receive damage whatsoever. Bards CAN however deal damage quite efficiently. I'm level 28 atm, and I can solo like crazy in SK at the spires. You see all the little druids kiting their gnolls and thinking they're cool, when a bard can charm a gnoll, sic it on another gnoll, wait for them both to get low health, and kill them both off, all losing only around half a bub of health, if executed correctly. Forget tanking and being a damage sponge, just use your fear song to fear kite, never taking any damage, or charm a mob and beat things down with it. Bards can deal damage all day long without dying, but if you're a bard in your teens and think you can keep up smacking things around and just running away with Selo's forever, think again. Bards DO have to resort to new methods later on, and sooner or later you won't be able to simply out-melee a white or maybe even a blue con. Hope it helps.<br><br>Fermata Lestrade<br>28 Bard, Altruistic Elite<br>Brell Serilis<br><br>"I see dumb people. They're everywhere...they don't even know that they're dumb. Some call them democrats."<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
