	   <tr><td colspan=2>[Alone, bards kindof stink (if you're looking at them from a warrior's perspective). They can't melee or deal significant damage, and they can't rapidly heal lost hitpoints. But a bard in a group makes a very strong group. Case in point...] <br><br>Not exactly true.  Untill lvl29 or so sure bards kind of weak on taking hits and dealing dmg as well but when you get your first charm song Bards are ultimate solo machines.  Granted that bard is a very nice addition to almost if not any grp. Using first charm song for charm kiting will take you from 29 to 39-40 (I myself was getting about 1 full yellow from charm kiting in Uthorks in EW, most were even or higher, in about 30 minutes with almost no down time)after that things get a bit more tricky since you have to use the next charm song that uses 20 mana but by that time you already have few dots that are dealing more and more dmg as you level (nice drums is a good thing to have to maximise the effect of dots) Currently I am level 51 and still using charm kite or dot snare kite. With Selos Drums at 51 I do about 160-180 points per tick twisting 4 songs, 3 dots and a snare.  I hope someone will find a usefull info in this chaotic response :)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
