<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100397008171415></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100397008171415><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=?class=4&mid=100397008171415>RE: ANSWER THIS PLZ</a> <a id=fs8 href=?class=4&mid=100397008171415#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=75748><span id= >Gruene</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 24th 8:34 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The main stats for Bards is DEX and CHA, but STR helps.  DEX affects how well a Bard plays his songs.  A Bard with high DEX will play a song longer, and without interruption, than a Bard with low DEX.<br><br>High CHA will lower prices in shops.  More importantly, high CHA will increase your chances of successfully mesmerizing of charming monsters do to you bidding.<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
